#: ../iot/attendance_system.rst:90
msgid "Set 2 LEDs as output and set the initial value to high."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/attendance_system.rst:106
msgid ""
"Use the ``get_time()`` function to get the current timestamp and return "
"two values. Where ``present_date`` is accurate to the day and "
"``present_time`` is accurate to the second."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/attendance_system.rst:119
msgid ""
"First, we set ``attendance`` to False, which means that no one is clocked"
" in."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/attendance_system.rst:121
msgid ""
"Then set GreenPin to low level to light it, and RedPin to high level to "
"keep it off, indicating that the current attendance system is working "
"normally."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/attendance_system.rst:123
msgid ""
"When someone punches in, the id and text information of the card will be "
"printed. If the red LED is on and the green LED is off, it means that the"
" check-in is successful and the result is sent to Cloud4RPi."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/attendance_system.rst:125
msgid ""
"During this period, the attendance system is in sleep state until the "
"next cycle starts (the green light is on)."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/attendance_system.rst:138
msgid ""
"First determine if the id is duplicated in ``attendance_list`` by an if "
"statement, if not, it means the punch-in is valid and pass the id "
"information into ``attendance_list``. Then we get the current timestamp "
"and use the id as the key of the ``attendance_statistics`` dictionary and"
" ``present_time`` as the value of the corresponding key. In this way, the"
" ``attendance_statistics`` dictionary stores the punch time of the "
"current id."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/attendance_system.rst:140
msgid ""
"Finally we write the ``attendance_statistics`` dictionary to a .csv file "
"and name the file as ``'attendance_sheet.'' + present_date + '.csv'``, so"
" that we store the attendance sheet in time order."
msgstr ""

#: ../iot/attendance_system.rst:144
msgid ""
"If you have written the person's name in the MFRC522 RFID, then replace "
"the ``id`` with ``text`` and your attendance sheet will record the name "
"of the person."
msgstr ""

